Description.val:
The primary roles of the aircraft are to conduct vertical replenishment, day/night ship-to-ship, ship-to-shore, and shore-to-ship external transfer of cargo; internal transport of passengers, mail and cargo, vertical onboard delivery; airhead operations, and day/night search and rescue.  Armed Helo and Airborne Mine Countermeasures (AMCM) have been added as primary mission areas for the MH-60S, being completed as block upgrades to the platform.  Armed Helo provides the Navy with organic Surface Warfare, Force Protection and Combat Search and Rescue capabilities.  Additional Armed Helo mission areas include Special Warfare Support, Maritime Interdiction Operations and Carrier Plane Guard.  Airborne Mine Countermeasures provides an Organic AMCM capability for the Littoral Combat Ship Mine Countermeasures Mission Package.  Secondary roles include torpedo and drone recovery, noncombatant evacuation operations, Navy SEAL and Explosive Ordnance Disposal support.

Note: Initial Spares Total is 176.165 vice 12.243

Justification.val:
Basis for FY2014 Budget Request:  The FY2014 request funds for the procurement of 18 aircraft and associated support.  The budget includes a follow-on joint Army-Navy 5-year Multiyear Procurement (MYP8) airframe contract for FY2012 - FY2016 and a Navy MH-60R & MH-60S (MYP2) for Mission Avionics/Common Cockpit for FY2012 - FY2016.  

Common Cockpit updated pricing reflects MYP2 award on 5 April 2012.  Airframe pricing reflects MYP8 contract award on 6 July 2012.
  
Government Furnished Equipment (GFE) Electronics contract award on the P-5a represents the Common Cockpit award; however, the unit price is incorrectly calculated based on the total GFE costs.

P-5 Notes:

Cost Element 1.1.3 Government Furnished Equipment (GFE) Electronics contract award represents the Common Cockpit award; however, the unit price is incorrectly calculated based on the total GFE costs.  Also, FY 2014 increase in GFE Electronics unit cost is due to costs associated with the compliance of the Pension Protection Act on the Lockheed Martin MYP contract.

Cost Element 1.2.1 Non Recurring Cost for FY2014 and FY2015 is budgeted for Production Line Shutdown efforts.  

Cost Element 1.2.2 Ancillary increase from FY2013 to FY2014 due to the procurement of additional armed helo ancillary kits for Fast Attack Craft (FAC)/Fast Insure Attack Craft (FIAC) threat defense.

Cost Element 2.1 Airframe Peculiar Ground Support Equipment (PGSE) increases for ECP incorporation and fielding of Airborne Mine Countermeasures ancillary equipment.  

Cost Element 2.4 Pec Training in FY2014 includes $10.6M to fund the West Coast Carriage, Stream, Tow, and Recovery System (CSTRS) Trainer and support system configuration upgrades to make the trainer concurrent with the latest production configuration.

Cost Element 2.4 Pub/Tech Eq increases to support Core Depot Standup for ancillary systems and production line shutdown requirements.
